Cell.Text: [S] G|Oh fine, go on... leave me here. When you decide to return to your senses, you know where to find me.

Node.Caption: DLC2HirelingQuestFollowerDismissTopic: It's time for us to part ways.

Cell.Text: [S] G|You're going ahead without me? Suit yourself...
[S] If it'll help us get moving quicker, sure.

Node.Caption: DLC2HirelingQuestFollowerTradeTopic: I need to trade some things with you.

Cell.Text: Did you still want me to help you or not?
[S] What do you have in mind?

Node.Caption: DLC2HirelingQuestFollowerFavorTopic: I need you to do something.

Cell.Text: Long story, but I don't see the harm in sharing it with you. | My last patron was a true Nord. He was dressed in animal skins, had tattoos on his face... a real traditional type, if you know what I mean. | He had an insatiable bloodlust and was extremely stubborn... one of the toughest employers I've ever had.

Node.Caption: DLC2HirelingQuestStoryBranchTopic: How did you end up on Solstheim?

Cell.Text: Simple... he paid well. Very well. | Anyway, we'd just cleared a ruined fort somewhere outside of Whiterun and when we got outside, we saw one of them galloping away on horseback. | Well, my boss wasn't about to let him get away, so we pursued... on foot, for three days.

Node.Caption: DLC2HirelingQuestStoryBranchTopic01: Why did you work for him then?

Cell.Text: Until we ended up tracking him to one of the largest bandit encampments I'd ever seen. | My patron took one look at me, and made the most menacing grin I'd ever seen. | At that moment, I knew I'd never see him again. No amount of money would ever be worth that kind of death.
